    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect sidelink slot processing in TX path\n\n### Summary\nIn the NR UE TX processing, when operating in sidelink mode (sl_mode == 2), not all uplink slots were being processed as sidelink slots due to an incorrect conditional check. This caused the UE to miss transmitting sidelink data in certain slot configurations.\n\nThe issue was caused by a copy-paste error from the RX processing logic where slot types are more varied. In TX processing for sidelink mode, ALL slots should be treated as sidelink slots.\n\n### Changes\n- `executables/nr-ue.c`: Modified the condition in `processSlotTX()` function to properly handle all uplink/mixed slots as sidelink slots when in sidelink mode.\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce this issue:\n1. Configure UE for sidelink mode (sl_mode = 2)\n2. Run UE with a configuration that has uplink or mixed slot types\n3. Observe that sidelink transmissions are not triggered for all expected slots\n4. Check logs for missing \"trigger L2 to run ue_sidelink_scheduler\" messages\n\nThe symptom is that sidelink data transmission is inconsistent and depends on the specific slot type values rather than properly processing all slots in sidelink mode.\n"
}